column3: Mostly for #14136 (and the ten other issues I closed with the same reported bug)

We would need major enhancements to support CoinJoin transactions. It's a lot more involved than just showing the correct "fee" (which this test would not check correctly anyway - some of the fee may be going to a CJ peer instead of the miner).
@luke-jr If this is unsupported, it should be documented as unsupported. See also my reply here: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19002#issuecomment-630236006
Should we document every other thing that isn't supported too?\n\nUnsupported is the default...
